<br>
It's not easy.  Anyone who has ever been on a Vox or Nagafen raid even, knows that it takes coordination to make sure everything runs smoothly.<br>
<br>
Today we ran what I considered to be a remarkably well run raid given the fact that it was, well, probably the largest damned raid that Everquest has ever seen.  We had over 200 people participating and, surprisingly, we had very few problems.<br>
<br>
But there were some disruptions.  There was on person who ninjaed one of the two items that dropped.  As has now been proved, the GMs do have the power to analyse the logs and locate ANY ITEM that has been looted from a corpse.  The person has been tracked down, the item removed from their inventory, actions taken against them and the item reimbursed to the rightful winner.  But the fact is WE SHOULDN'T HAVE HAD A NINJA IN THE FIRST PLACE!<br>
<br>
But I don't want to hear people spreading runors about who the looter was because, at the end of the day, only the looter and the GM know for certain.  The GMs refused to confirm the name to me so I can only guess and I am not going to spread what amount to unsubstantiated rumors about anybody on gme, so please do not ask me.<br>
<br>
So what is the next gripe?  Why, it's the peopel who rolled multiple times when asked to roll on the items.  did you really think that in a raid the size of which we ran there would not be safeguards to make certain people who rolled multiple times would get away with it scot free?  Now the majority of people were playing by the rules but some thought they could get away with multiple rolls.  People like Richie, Curve, Araefel, Alfra, Vsalrhal etc etc.  I have full logs showing everyone who rolled multiple times and you are ALL on notice.  By all means come along to one of these raids again but if you try any of that @#%$ next time you will be banned from all further raids of this type.<br>
<br>
And finally, as always, there are the gripers.  Those people who have nothing better to do in their short, sad litle lives than to find fault with everything that goes on around them.  Again, mercifully, there were VERY few people who had their heads lodged up their own arses in this respect but every single one of them made the event like pulling teeth.  As I said at the start of the raid...<br>
<br>
