<br>
Simply put, I had tells all last night asking me if the ninja looter had been found and if action had been taken.  As soon as the GMs had informed me that the matter had been cleared everyone wnated to knwo who the ninja looter was.  Well, I didn't know and I still don't know.  But this didn't stop the rumors from flying.  I had 3 people flat out swear that they <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>knew</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> who the ninja was, even though it was two different people, and so to quell the rumors I decided to post both of them up at the same time, showing that there was actually no way that it could have been both of them and so therefore hopefully killing both rumors at the same time.<br>
<br>
And Araefel, sorry if the lag was so bad you had to roll twice.  As you can appreciate it was pretty dire for all concerned.  And if I got over-excited (which I know I do and I know I did) it was mainly because it was almost impossible to control everyone and I wanted to avoid situations which would allow nastiness to happen.  Like the ninjaing of loot.  As Pan pointed out, with that many people the random number method was about the only practical way we had of doing loot given the time we had left on the corpse.  It actually worked rather well, all things concidered.<br>
<br>
There are lessons to be learned for all concerned on this one, but at the end of the day we achieved our objectives and I think the majority had quite a bit of fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=panamah>Panamah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><HR><font color=#FF0000>Drinal Ally</font><HR></span><br>  Posts: 507<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/19/03 8:33:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2012.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://nmcs.com/kingscourt/images/panamah_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /flame raid disruptions</span><hr size=1> Couple of problems preventing Ninja's.  First off, we had to handle the planar projection hailing and that need to happen fast since he's only up for a short while.  So people had to change raids.  Trewayn probably lost his lock on the corpse when he went to do that.  <br>
